First it's an individual right.Second the intent of the Second amendment was clarified by the Federalist papers as well as many personal writings from the founding fathers that wrote it.You are attempting to twist the intent and definition of what a militia is. And you are incorrect. A militia is an group of able bodied men as defined by the Constitution that are assembled by private citizens (the people) to defend the state against all enemies both foreign and domestic.Penn and Teller define it very well:   http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1GNu7ldL1LM&feature=related  